5% longevity bonus by 50 hitpoints (its not always 50, its a formula based on con and some magical other numbers... the instance is as low as 30 in some cases), in the current state of the game of mass damage thanks to realm skills.. works out to what?  One third damage from a swing?  8% absorbsion from a common spell?  If you break down the average time of a fight, 5% longevity bonus would roughly equal .5 - 1.5 seconds, not even enough time to get in an extra style.<br>
<br>
2handers are useful in rare situations.  So is distraction, and danger sense =)  the word &quot;liability&quot; pops up alot, because if using a 2hander shouldnt be factored in as a class defining bonus =) If it is factored in as that, then yes, its a liability. (since there are many other more desireable options for a class bonus)<br>
<br>
