 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/02 3:19:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3657.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ashame this makes perfect sense...</span><hr size=1> I still have to disagree with upping the points.<br>
<br>
My proposal of adding 12.5% to the primary would increase the base damage of the primary weapon by 20%, or 10% boost in overall melee damage (I would up both primary and LA by 15%, but I would like to see the effects of the scaled down version first).<br>
<br>
An Infiltrator can have:<br>
50 Thrust<br>
15 Dual Wield<br>
For the same amount of points it takes a Shadowblade to have:<br>
34 Axe<br>
39 Left Axe<br>
<br>
It's already proven that Shadowblades have to spread out their melee points more evenly to maximize their damage potential. The Infiltrator's bonus points can be spent to raise Dual Wield to 33%, which adds 6.2% to the overall melee damage. It isn't that high, because the Infiltrator spent it in a specialization with diminished returns. It can range anywhere from a 6% to 28% melee damage bonus for the Infiltrator, so that is why I use 15% as a good figure from which to work with (or +7dps) to get Shadowblades and Nightshades to measure to catch up.<br>
<br>
Even with the above mentioned template, and multiplying the result by x1.05 to account for Shadowblade hit points, Infiltrators still come slightly on top (that is why it could possibly need a 15% boost to both weapons by level 50, but I would wait and see with the effects of 12.5% first). One of the argument to give Shadowblades more points is the utility that Infiltrator can get through added points. Instead, I suggest analyzing the styles you can obtain with your points (34-44 range) and looking to make those worthwhile to add more utility. (For example, longer stun on Frosty Gaze or better damage, or removing the 25 detaunt and returning it to the base of the chain for Atrophy and reserving 25 for another style, or looking at Swords and Axe styles that are redundant). That way, you get the added damage + hit points + utility without having needed any more specialization poitns.<br>
<br>
...and it's okay if LA is slightly less damaging in base damage in DW...<br>
<br>
I never ended up posting the results of the style damage in all my NS vs SB tests because it takes so long to crunch, only to get flamed or misread by board trolls, but this simplifies some of the data collected:<br>
<br>
For the Shadowblade:<br>
Garrote adds 75% damage to the primary at 34 + 2 (36) CS, and 34 + 2 (36) Sword<br>
Doublefrost adds 175% damage to the primary at 34 + 2 (36) LA<br>
<br>
For the Nightshade:<br>
Garrote adds 68% damage to the primary at 50 + 5 (55) CS, and 34 + 3 (37) Pierce<br>
<br>
And my formulas almost proved the way base damage is calculated. Styled damage is still a relative unknown that I'm learning more about, and I've been working with it more lately and testing CS damage caps and such.<br>
<br>
The Nightshade result (yeah, that's me!) had me scratchig my head! How could my Garrote do less damage for having +19 CS ?? (and that was after normalizing damage from resistances) I'm attributing it to Nightshade Quickness effects on damage, since I have a base of +40 QUI than the Shadowblade has, but that's a seperate issue altogether for Nightshades to wrestle with when it comes to their style damage. (My testing basically proved Nightshade base damage to be fairly decent, while something was left to be desired in SB base damage. That was why I proposed base fixes for the damage back then. It was style damage that shocked me because I originally thought my garrotes were returning more damage, but after normalizing for resistances and taking into consideration my +19 CS bonus, it caught me off guard that I did less garrote damage).<br>
<br>
The point of the comparison is that the best use anytime tool available to the Infiltrator is Garrote for 75% added damage. The best tool available for Shadowblades still adds 175% added damage (and this was before the left axe level based scaling boost).<br>
<br>
but Infiltrators get Dragonfang... which is the best evade counter style in the game...<br>
but Shadowblades get Doubleforst... which is the most damage use anytime style in the game...<br>
but Nightshades get a poor man's Dragonfang (Diamondback), and a 4 chain use anytime combo /snicker<br>
<br>
You can see where I am going with on tradeoffs here when it comes to style. Dragonfang looks awesome, and those extra points make it just as easy to obtain as it does for a Shadowblade to spend 34 points to obtain Left Axe and dish out +175% additional damage, and Infiltrators have nothing like it. It burns endurance, but it does layeth the smack down in 1v1 when it is needed, and is still widely used.<br>
<br>
<b>To summarize it all up, my point is:</b><br>
<br>
With the base damage proposal of 12.5% to the primary by level 50, and appx +50hp by level 50, your damage output will be more than fine and in the ballpark of being made up for having less points. If you are looking for added utility that the Infiltrator obtains with those points (ie Dragonfang), no amount of specialization points will ever grant Shadowblades that ability, it simply doesn't exist in Midgard. Instead, focus on the styles you can obtain with your points and look to make them more worthwhile to you. It is very unlikely Mythic will add anymore specialization points for Shadowblades, or any class for that matter. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A> at: 7/1/02 3:23:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ubalorgafdan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balor Gafdan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/02 7:48:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3657.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theblackwatch.biz/Balor.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ashame this makes perfect sense...</span><hr size=1> Unfortuantely Elaa, you'll never be listened to.  }:)<br>
